<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="299" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">
This species has previously been included by the majority of authors in the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Diagramma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diagramma" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Diagramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Oken, 1817, but recent phylogenetic analyses (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2966.1.4" author="Sanciangco, MD" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="37 - 50" refId="B41" refString="Sanciangco, MD, Rocha, LA, Carpenter, KE, 2011. A molecular phylogeny of the grunts (Perciformes: Haemulidae) inferred using mitochondrial and nuclear genes. Zootaxa 2966: 37 - 50, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2966.1.4" title="A molecular phylogeny of the grunts (Perciformes: Haemulidae) inferred using mitochondrial and nuclear genes." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2966.1.4" volume="2966" year="2011">Sanciangco et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-12-57" author="Tavera, J" journalOrPublisher="Trends in Ecology and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" refId="B48" refString="Tavera, J, Acero, A, Balart, E, Bernardi, G, 2012. Molecular phylogeny of grunts (Teleostei, Haemulidae), with an emphasis on the ecology, evolution, and speciation history of New World species. BMC Evolutionary Biology 12: 57. https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-12-57" title="Molecular phylogeny of grunts (Teleostei, Haemulidae), with an emphasis on the ecology, evolution, and speciation history of New World species. BMC Evolutionary Biology 12: 57." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-12-57" year="2012">Tavera et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.12.032" author="Tavera, J" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="213 - 223" refId="B49" refString="Tavera, J, Acero, PA, Wainwright, PC, 2018. Multilocus phylogeny, divergence times, and a major role for the benthic-to-pelagic axis in the diversification of grunts (Haemulidae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 121: 213 - 223, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.12.032" title="Multilocus phylogeny, divergence times, and a major role for the benthic-to-pelagic axis in the diversification of grunts (Haemulidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.12.032" volume="121" year="2018">Tavera et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
) have shown that 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Diagramma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diagramma" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Diagramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(including type species 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. pictus" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">D. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is deeply nested within 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and sister to its type species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacepede" authorityYear="1801" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus chaetodonoides" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chaetodonoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus chaetodonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacepède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
, 1801), and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.12.032" author="Tavera, J" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="213 - 223" refId="B49" refString="Tavera, J, Acero, PA, Wainwright, PC, 2018. Multilocus phylogeny, divergence times, and a major role for the benthic-to-pelagic axis in the diversification of grunts (Haemulidae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 121: 213 - 223, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.12.032" title="Multilocus phylogeny, divergence times, and a major role for the benthic-to-pelagic axis in the diversification of grunts (Haemulidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2017.12.032" volume="121" year="2018">Tavera et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
have proposed that 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Diagramma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diagramma" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Diagramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacepède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
, 1801. As pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Parenti, P" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal of Ichthyology" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="150 - 196" refId="B32" refString="Parenti, P, 2019. An annotated checklist of the fishes of the family Haemulidae (Teleostei: Perciformes). Iranian Journal of Ichthyology 6 (3): 150 - 196" title="An annotated checklist of the fishes of the family Haemulidae (Teleostei: Perciformes)." volume="6" year="2019">Parenti (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, however, accepting 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Diagramma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diagramma" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Diagramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
creates several nomenclatural problems: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1792" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus pictus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Tortonese, 1936) becomes a secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. pictus" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Thunberg, 1792), and the next available name for 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. pictus" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Tortonese) is 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus cinctus subsp. punctatatus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="cinctus" subSpecies="punctatatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus cinctus punctatatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fang, 1942 (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke, R" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" publicationUrl="http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/ichthyology/catalog/fishcatmain.asp" refId="B10" refString="Fricke, R, Eschmeyer, WN, Van der Laan, R, 2021b. Eschmeyer's catalog of Fishes: genera, species, references. California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco, CA, USA. [Accessed on 23 April 2021] http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/ichthyology/catalog/fishcatmain.asp" title="Eschmeyer's catalog of Fishes: genera, species, references. California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco, CA, USA. [Accessed on 23 April 2021]" url="http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/ichthyology/catalog/fishcatmain.asp" year="2021 b">Fricke et al. 2021b</bibRefCitation>
) which is secondarily preoccupied in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Diagramma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diagramma puncatatum" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="puncatatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Diagramma puncatatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cuvier, 1830 (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke, R" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" publicationUrl="http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/ichthyology/catalog/fishcatmain.asp" refId="B10" refString="Fricke, R, Eschmeyer, WN, Van der Laan, R, 2021b. Eschmeyer's catalog of Fishes: genera, species, references. California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco, CA, USA. [Accessed on 23 April 2021] http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/ichthyology/catalog/fishcatmain.asp" title="Eschmeyer's catalog of Fishes: genera, species, references. California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco, CA, USA. [Accessed on 23 April 2021]" url="http://researcharchive.calacademy.org/research/ichthyology/catalog/fishcatmain.asp" year="2021 b">Fricke et al. 2021b</bibRefCitation>
). This problem was long ago recognized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Whitley, GP" journalOrPublisher="Series B, Biological Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" refId="B55" refString="Whitley, GP, 1951. New fish names and records. Proceedings of the Royal Zoological Society of New South Wales 1949-1950: 61-68." title="New fish names and records. Proceedings of the Royal Zoological Society of New South Wales 1949 - 1950: 61 - 68." year="1951">Whitley (1951)</bibRefCitation>
, who anticipated 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Diagramma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diagramma" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Diagramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and accordingly proposed the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus fangi" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fangi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus fangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Whitley, 1951, as a replacement for 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. cinctus subsp. punctatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="subSpecies" species="cinctus" subSpecies="punctatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">P. cinctus punctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fang (a species not yet recorded from the Bay of Bengal). Thus, we regard 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1792" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus pictus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Thunberg, 1792) as the correct name for the species described here from Bangladesh.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. pictus" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Bay of Bengal are part of a distinct subspecies, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus pictus subsp. cinerascens" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="pictus" subSpecies="cinerascens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus pictus cinerascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cuvier, 1830-one of five geographically separate subspecies recognized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, JW" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Queensland Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="657 - 676" refId="B19" refString="Johnson, JW, Randall, JE, Chenoweth, SF, 2001. Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum 46 (2): 657 - 676" title="Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review." volume="46" year="2001">Johnson et al. (2001</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Diagramma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diagramma" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Diagramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="pictus" genus="P." lsidName="P. pictus subsp. pictus" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="subSpecies" species="pictus" subSpecies="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">P. pictus pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Thunberg), 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. pictus subsp. labiosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="subSpecies" species="pictus" subSpecies="labiosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">P. pictus labiosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Macleay, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. pictus subsp. punctatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="subSpecies" species="pictus" subSpecies="punctatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">P. pictus punctatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cuvier, and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. pictus subsp. centurio" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" rank="subSpecies" species="pictus" subSpecies="centurio">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">P. pictus centurio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cuvier). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1792" class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus pictus" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, subspecies 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus pictus subsp. cinerascens" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="pictus" subSpecies="cinerascens">Plectorhinchus pictus cinerascens</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, JW" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Queensland Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="657 - 676" refId="B19" refString="Johnson, JW, Randall, JE, Chenoweth, SF, 2001. Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum 46 (2): 657 - 676" title="Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review." volume="46" year="2001">Johnson et al. (2001)</bibRefCitation>
differs from all others in the configuration of the body stripes of juveniles, size of spots, and nature of the lines on the cheeks and operculum of large juveniles to small adults. Juveniles of about 150 mm TL often have broad, clearly defined body stripes, not yet beginning to break into broken lines or numerous spots; and progress from a striped to a fully spotted phase at 180-240 mm TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, JW" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Queensland Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="657 - 676" refId="B19" refString="Johnson, JW, Randall, JE, Chenoweth, SF, 2001. Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum 46 (2): 657 - 676" title="Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review." volume="46" year="2001">Johnson et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5). A more detailed genetic study is necessary to determine whether this geographically distinct color variety should be afforded separate species recognition (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, JW" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Queensland Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="657 - 676" refId="B19" refString="Johnson, JW, Randall, JE, Chenoweth, SF, 2001. Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum 46 (2): 657 - 676" title="Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review." volume="46" year="2001">Johnson et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="299" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Haemulidae" genus="Plectorhinchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plectorhinchus pictus subsp. cinerascens" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="pictus" subSpecies="cinerascens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Plectorhinchus pictus cinerascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, occurs from the Bay of Bengal to the Arabian/Persian Gulf (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, JW" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Queensland Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="299" pagination="657 - 676" refId="B19" refString="Johnson, JW, Randall, JE, Chenoweth, SF, 2001. Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum 46 (2): 657 - 676" title="Diagramma melanacrum, new species of haemulid fish from Indonesia, Borneo and the Philippines with a generic review." volume="46" year="2001">Johnson et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="299" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="299">Not yet assessed, not listed in the IUCN Red List of Threatened Species (https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/123439745/123494892).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
